# Database Access with Drizzle

All database interactions must go through the Drizzle `db` client and the typed schema. Never use raw SQL strings or query the database directly.

## Setup

- DB client: `src/lib/db/db.ts` → `import { db } from "@/lib/db/db"`
- Schema tables: `src/lib/db/schema.ts` → `import { decks, cards } from "@/lib/db/schema"`

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — raw SQL
const result = await sql`SELECT * FROM decks WHERE clerk_user_id = ${userId}`;

// ✅ GOOD — Drizzle query builder
import { db } from "@/lib/db/db";
import { decks } from "@/lib/db/schema";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";

const userDecks = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));
```

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — insert
await db.insert(cards).values({ deckId, front, back });

// ✅ GOOD — update
await db.update(decks).set({ title }).where(eq(decks.id, deckId));

// ✅ GOOD — delete
await db.delete(cards).where(eq(cards.id, cardId));
```

## Schema Changes

To add tables or columns, edit `src/lib/db/schema.ts` and generate a migration:

```bash
npx drizzle-kit generate
npx drizzle-kit migrate
```
